findings.recommended_fix:
Collect decoded bytes into a Vec<u8>, then use `String::from_utf8_lossy` or `String::from_utf8` to convert to a String. Example:
```rust
pub fn percent_decode_path(s: &str) -> String {
    let bytes: Vec<u8> = /* hex-decode loop producing Vec<u8> */;
    String::from_utf8_lossy(&bytes).into_owned()
}
```
Alternatively, use the well-tested `percent-encoding` crate.

Use explicit checked conversions:
```rust
let width = u32::try_from(img_data.width)
    .map_err(|_| anyhow::anyhow!("image width too large for u32"))?;
let height = u32::try_from(img_data.height)
    .map_err(|_| anyhow::anyhow!("image height too large for u32"))?;
```

Move the description to the first `///` line:
```rust
/// State for the interactive `/lsp discover` dialog.
///
/// Shown as an overlay...
```

Define an enum (or u8 constants) to represent the health states:
```rust
mod provider_health_state {
    pub const UNCHECKED: u8 = 0;
    pub const AVAILABLE: u8 = 1;
    pub const UNAVAILABLE: u8 = 2;
}
```
Or use an `AtomicU8` wrapper type with typed accessor methods.
